\title{Gwas Database}

\taxon{skill}

\meta{description}{"Query NHGRI-EBI GWAS Catalog for SNP-trait associations. Search variants by rs ID, disease/trait, gene, retrieve p-values and summary statistics, for genetic epidemiology and polygenic risk scores."}

\subtree{
\title{GWAS Catalog Database}
\subtree{
\title{Overview}
\p{The GWAS Catalog is a comprehensive repository of published genome-wide association studies maintained by the National Human Genome Research Institute (NHGRI) and the European Bioinformatics Institute (EBI). The catalog contains curated SNP-trait associations from thousands of GWAS publications, including genetic variants, associated traits and diseases, p-values, effect sizes, and full summary statistics for many studies.}
}

\subtree{
\title{When to Use This Skill}
\p{This skill should be used when queries involve:}

\ul{
\li{\strong{Genetic variant associations}: Finding SNPs associated with diseases or traits}
\li{\strong{SNP lookups}: Retrieving information about specific genetic variants (rs IDs)}
\li{\strong{Trait/disease searches}: Discovering genetic associations for phenotypes}
\li{\strong{Gene associations}: Finding variants in or near specific genes}
\li{\strong{GWAS summary statistics}: Accessing complete genome-wide association data}
\li{\strong{Study metadata}: Retrieving publication and cohort information}
\li{\strong{Population genetics}: Exploring ancestry-specific associations}
\li{\strong{Polygenic risk scores}: Identifying variants for risk prediction models}
\li{\strong{Functional genomics}: Understanding variant effects and genomic context}
\li{\strong{Systematic reviews}: Comprehensive literature synthesis of genetic associations}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Core Capabilities}
\subtree{
\title{1. Understanding GWAS Catalog Data Structure}
\p{The GWAS Catalog is organized around four core entities:}

\ul{
\li{\strong{Studies}: GWAS publications with metadata (PMID, author, cohort details)}
\li{\strong{Associations}: SNP-trait associations with statistical evidence (p ≤ 5×10⁻⁸)}
\li{\strong{Variants}: Genetic markers (SNPs) with genomic coordinates and alleles}
\li{\strong{Traits}: Phenotypes and diseases (mapped to EFO ontology terms)}
}

\p{\strong{Key Identifiers:}}

\ul{
\li{Study accessions: \code{\startverb GCST\stopverb} IDs (e.g., GCST001234)}
\li{Variant IDs: \code{\startverb rs\stopverb} numbers (e.g., rs7903146) or \code{\startverb variant_id\stopverb} format}
\li{Trait IDs: EFO terms (e.g., EFO_0001360 for type 2 diabetes)}
\li{Gene symbols: HGNC approved names (e.g., TCF7L2)}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{2. Web Interface Searches}
\p{The web interface at https://www.ebi.ac.uk/gwas/ supports multiple search modes:}

\p{\strong{By Variant (rs ID):}}

\pre{\startverb
rs7903146
\stopverb}

\p{Returns all trait associations for this SNP.}

\p{\strong{By Disease/Trait:}}

\pre{\startverb
type 2 diabetes
Parkinson disease
body mass index
\stopverb}

\p{Returns all associated genetic variants.}

\p{\strong{By Gene:}}

\pre{\startverb
APOE
TCF7L2
\stopverb}

\p{Returns variants in or near the gene region.}

\p{\strong{By Chromosomal Region:}}

\pre{\startverb
10:114000000-115000000
\stopverb}

\p{Returns variants in the specified genomic interval.}

\p{\strong{By Publication:}}

\pre{\startverb
PMID:20581827
Author: McCarthy MI
GCST001234
\stopverb}

\p{Returns study details and all reported associations.}
}

\subtree{
\title{3. REST API Access}
\p{The GWAS Catalog provides two REST APIs for programmatic access:}

\p{\strong{Base URLs:}}

\ul{
\li{GWAS Catalog API: \code{\startverb https://www.ebi.ac.uk/gwas/rest/api\stopverb}}
\li{Summary Statistics API: \code{\startverb https://www.ebi.ac.uk/gwas/summary-statistics/api\stopverb}}
}

\p{\strong{API Documentation:}}

\ul{
\li{Main API docs: https://www.ebi.ac.uk/gwas/rest/docs/api}
\li{Summary stats docs: https://www.ebi.ac.uk/gwas/summary-statistics/docs/}
}

\p{\strong{Core Endpoints:}}

\ol{
\li{\strong{Studies endpoint} - \code{\startverb /studies/{accessionID}\stopverb}}
}

